Home Box Office, Inc. (HBO), is a unit of Time Warner Inc., and is headquartered in New York City. HBO has more than 40 million subscribers and broadcasts concerts, stand-up comedy, theatrical movies, and sports all without commercials or censor… MoreHome Box Office, Inc. (HBO), is a unit of Time Warner Inc., and is headquartered in New York City. HBO has more than 40 million subscribers and broadcasts concerts, stand-up comedy, theatrical movies, and sports all without commercials or censor restrictions.
IT Priorities:
• Home Box Office, Inc. is expanding into a hybrid cloud environment.
• HBO would like to expand its disaster recovery plan.
• The company is expanding its bring your own device (BYOD) policy in the near future.

IT Structure
As a major… MoreIT Priorities:
• Home Box Office, Inc. is expanding into a hybrid cloud environment.
• HBO would like to expand its disaster recovery plan.
• The company is expanding its bring your own device (BYOD) policy in the near future.

IT Structure
As a major media company, Home Box Office, Inc. maintains technical staff supporting internal IT functions as well as media delivery platforms. The majority of HBO's technical staff work in New York, NY. The company also has some regional IT assets for a Latin American division as well as a Western US division. The company is working to standardize IT with its parent company, Time Warner. Despite this, the companies maintain separate IT staff and are profiled separately in RainKing.

IT Vendors:
• HBO uses Oracle for database and eBusiness functions.





